</div>
</div>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: CAMPSITE RESERVATION</strong></h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Nature Park Services, how may I help you today?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Hello, I’m calling to make a campsite reservation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Great, let me just pull up the reservation form and we can get started.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Okay, first, could I get your name?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Sure, it’s Sandra Camp.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> All right, Miss Camp. I can make reservations for the Northern, Central, and Southern California parks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Which region will you be traveling to?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Is Mount Laguna in the central or southern region?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Is that where you’re going? Yes, that’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(Q1) Southern</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Do you know which campground?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Actually, I was hoping you could help me with that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">I’ve read a lot about two different campgrounds: Sunrise and Mountain, but I can’t decide.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Mountain Campground has many hiking trails close by, but then again, Sunrise Campground is next to the lake and my husband loves to fish.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Hmm, they’re both really beautiful spots.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">I guess it depends on when you’re going, really.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, we’re going in April.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> The thing is, fishing at Sunrise Campground is only allowed from June to September, so I suggest <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q2) Mountain</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay, then that makes it easy. So we’ve selected the campground.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">So now we need to think about which sort of site.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">There are different options: you can stay at a cabin, a tent, or a recreational vehicle campsite.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Which type of site offers the most peace and quiet?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> A <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">(Q3) tent</strong> site would be your best bet.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> That sounds good to me.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\">Um, so if you’ve read about the park, you probably know that some vehicles aren’t suitable for the park roads.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\">Cars tend to get stuck when it rains.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\">If you have a <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"14\">(Q4) truck</strong>, you won’t have any trouble.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Luckily, we do, and we’ll be driving that instead of our car.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\">I hope we don’t get any rain, but I’d rather be safe than sorry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Perfect. I’ll just need to get your license plate number.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">(Q5) QY0918</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Thanks. And what about your trip dates?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> We’d like to stay for three days.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Does that mean you’ll be staying two nights?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> That’s right. We’ll be arriving on April 10th and leaving on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">(Q6) twelfth</strong> (April 12th).</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<h2 data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS</strong></h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Now, the park is home to some black bears, so you’ll need to rent a bear-proof food container to lock your food inside for hikes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\">It’s really just a precaution. We have small, medium, and large food containers for campers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Oh, I’m familiar with food containers, but they can be heavy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"42\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, the large one is, but if you get the <strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">(Q7) small</strong> size, it’s not so heavy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"43\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Oh, let’s do that. I really want something lightweight.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"44\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"44\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Would you be interested in signing up for a guided nature walk on the second day of your trip?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"45\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> A what kind of walk?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"46\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"46\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Well, at 7:00 AM, there are three different ones near your campground:</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"47\">There’s the flower walk, the bird watching walk, and the waterfall walk.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"48\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Really? I love gardening, so the <strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">(Q8) flower</strong> walk sounds interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"49\">My son might be more into the waterfall one, but I can’t imagine him getting up in time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"50\">Maybe I could go alone. Could you sign me up?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"51\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"51\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Sure. Now, just a few more things.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"52\">Visitors must purchase park passes as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"53\">You have the option of the one-day pass, which would be cheaper, or the <strong data-path-to-node=\"53\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(Q9) one-year</strong> pass, which is a better deal if you plan to go to more parks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"54\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"54\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Let’s go ahead and get that. I’m sure we’ll visit more parks soon. It’s a really good bargain.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"55\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"55\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Plus, we donate $5 of the pass fee to one of our three park programs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"56\">You get to choose which one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"57\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"57\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Park programs?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"58\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"58\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Yes, well, we run a <strong data-path-to-node=\"58\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">(Q10) youth</strong> program for local kids to attend a nature camp in the summer.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"59\">The other two options are conservation projects: there’s a wildlife program and a tree planting program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"60\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"60\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sandra:</strong> Wow, they all sound worthwhile. What should I do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"61\">Um, it’s important for children to appreciate the outdoors.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"62\">Let’s go with the youth program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"63\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"63\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Employee:</strong> Okay, we just need to review the fee and payment information.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3cbc3b3a-333d-48ab-8720-38b4400f4a51', '74e02f7d-c30a-456e-9520-be5078b82771', 'radio', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "People have mistaken opinions about fishing hooks'' functions."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Fishing is more difficult in New Zealand than Pacific islands."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Maoris use new materials to build hooks after they arrived New Zealand."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Maoris'' hooks are limited in forms because of the material limitation it used."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The fishing line of Maoris is worse than the European."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Europeans are given fishing hooks as a gift from local Maoris."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "According to WA, Maoris have already engaged in crop growing."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Hooks of Maoris are functioned in the same way to the hooks of European."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. People have mistaken opinions about fishing hooks’ functions. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…for many centuries, their <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">true purpose was misunderstood</strong>… Many assumed these… hooks served only <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">decorative, ceremonial, or ritualistic</strong> purposes…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Suốt nhiều thế kỷ, mục đích thực sự của lưỡi câu bị hiểu lầm. Nhiều người cho rằng chúng chỉ để trang trí hay làm lễ nghi, trong khi thực tế chúng là công cụ đánh cá cực kỳ chuẩn xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Fishing is more difficult in New Zealand than Pacific islands. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> Chỉ nói khi đến New Zealand, họ thấy môi trường giàu tài nguyên và họ thích nghi nhanh chóng.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">không hề so sánh</strong> độ khó của việc đánh cá giữa New Zealand và các đảo Thái Bình Dương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Maoris use new materials to build hooks after they arrived New Zealand. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“They quickly adapted by using <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">familiar materials</strong> such as bones and stones…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài nói họ dùng các nguyên liệu <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">quen thuộc</strong> (familiar) như xương và đá, chứ không phải nguyên liệu “mới” (new). (Họ chỉ dùng nguyên liệu mới là kim loại sau khi người châu Âu đến ở thế kỷ 18).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Maoris’ hooks are limited in forms because of the material limitation it used. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…their form was somewhat <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">limited</strong>. This was because the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">materials… could not be forged or bent like metal</strong>, thus <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">restricting the range of shapes</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hình dáng lưỡi câu bị giới hạn vì chất liệu (xương, đá) không thể rèn hay uốn như kim loại. Điều này khớp hoàn toàn với câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. The fishing line of Maoris is worse than the European. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Their fishing lines… proved <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">just as strong—if not stronger—than those used by Europeans</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dây câu của người Māori bền bằng, thậm chí là bền hơn của người châu Âu, chứ không phải tệ hơn (worse).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Europeans are given fishing hooks as a gift from local Maoris. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3 &amp; 5):</strong> Có nói người châu Âu thấy các công cụ này khi thám hiểm, và sau này có việc trao đổi kim loại/kim đóng tàu.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">không nhắc đến</strong> việc người Māori tặng lưỡi câu như một món quà (gift) cho người châu Âu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. According to WA (William Anderson), Maoris have already engaged in crop growing. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In 1777… William Anderson… noted that… the Māori had already developed advanced methods of <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">intensive farming</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> William Anderson ghi nhận người Māori đã có các phương pháp thâm canh (intensive farming), tức là trồng trọt (crop growing).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Hooks of Maoris are functioned in the same way to the hooks of European. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Māori fishing hooks <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">functioned quite differently</strong> from those used by Europeans. Rather than piercing directly… Māori hooks worked by <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">rotating</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lưỡi câu Māori hoạt động theo cơ chế xoay, khác hoàn toàn (differently) với cơ chế đâm xuyên trực tiếp của người châu Âu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('60e314e2-1faf-47b6-98c6-f033fae95213', '4237e5ff-6c2e-4787-8cdb-cbd8d42cd61b', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. asked a lot of questions"}, {"option_text": "B. misunderstood an explanation"}, {"option_text": "C. learned some new information"}], "question": "During the lecture about restoration and types of paint, Jenny"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. deciding the cause of damage to the portrait"}, {"option_text": "B. imagining what the restored portrait would look like"}, {"option_text": "C. choosing the best method for restoring the portrait"}], "question": "What do the students think will be the most difficult part of their assignment?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the visit was inspiring"}, {"option_text": "B. the restorer''s work was exhausting"}, {"option_text": "C. the subject matter of the picture was interesting"}], "question": "When discussing their trip to the restorer''s studio, the students agree that"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. feature local scenes"}, {"option_text": "B. are by well-known artists"}, {"option_text": "C. show famous people"}], "question": "Jenny thinks that the authorities give priority to restoring paintings which"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0f5b10d9-7e0d-4afa-829e-07205cd880bd', '4237e5ff-6c2e-4787-8cdb-cbd8d42cd61b', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p data-start="939" data-end="1011"><strong data-start="939" data-end="1011">What comment do the students make about each of the following books?</strong></p>
<p data-start="1013" data-end="1112">Choose <strong data-start="1020" data-end="1027">SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-start="1079" data-end="1086">A–H</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<h3 data-section-id=\"6xbvdo\" data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"470\">Books</h3>\n<p>25. Bringing Old Pictures Back to Life {C too basic to be of much use}</p>\n<p>26. Preserving Masterpieces {G focuses on historical aspects}</p>\n<p>27. Saving Paintings {F requires scientific knowledge}</p>\n<p>28. Approaches to Restoration {D deals with modern techniques}</p>\n<p>29. Art Conservation Today {B useful tips on preventing problems}</p>\n<p>30. Restoring Fine Art {A good visuals}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A good visuals"}, {"optionText": "B useful tips on preventing problems"}, {"optionText": "C too basic to be of much use"}, {"optionText": "D deals with modern techniques"}, {"optionText": "E rather out of date"}, {"optionText": "F requires scientific knowledge"}, {"optionText": "G focuses on historical aspects"}, {"optionText": "H wide international coverage"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('19d5b71c-4ac6-4e1c-806d-07ecb8f5f3b8', 'eeda12b4-6923-4479-ad48-e929a1adcbb1', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p data-path-to-node="2"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="0">Film Club</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="3"><strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="0">Membership information</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="4">Club meets every 2 weeks</p>
<p data-path-to-node="5">No {age} limit</p>
<p data-path-to-node="6">Student membership costs £{21.50} per season</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7">Members get:</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="8">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="8,0,0">free entry to club films</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="8,1,0">£{2} reduction on other films at cinema</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="9">Members are entitled to 3 hours'' free {parking}</p>
<p data-path-to-node="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Films to be shown:</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="0">Oct 14: <em data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="8">Pablo</em></strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="12">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="12,0,0">about a child in {Argentina} who runs away from home and wins a {singing} competition on TV</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="13"><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">Oct 28: <em data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="8">The Soldier</em></strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,0,0">with live {piano} accompaniment</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,1,0">made in the year {1922}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,2,0">type of film: a {comedy}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="15"><strong data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="0">Nov 11: <em data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="8">Tiger</em></strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="16">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,0,0">cartoon aimed at adults</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,1,0">followed by a {talk}<strong> </strong>by the director</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7100968a-8296-4b0d-afb2-67520d5ab08e', '18d88cc6-78d3-4e76-9481-8f27485e317b', 'matching', 'Questions 11-16', '', '<p>Which comment does John make about each of the following photography magazines?</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="87">SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="142">A-H</strong>, next to questions 11-16.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-84\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-995 citation-996 citation-end-996\">Photography magazines<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-995 citation-end-995\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"11\"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-85\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><span class=\"citation-993 citation-994 citation-end-994\">Camera Ready {B. Easy to understand advice}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"12\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-993 citation-end-993\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"13\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-86\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><span class=\"citation-991 citation-992 citation-end-992\">Outdoor Lens {F. High quality photos}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"14\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-991 citation-end-991\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"15\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-87\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><span class=\"citation-989 citation-990 citation-end-990\">Photographer Today {D. Reports about new products}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"16\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-989 citation-end-989\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"17\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-88\" data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><span class=\"citation-987 citation-988 citation-end-988\">Photo Now {A. Useful technical advice}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"18\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-987 citation-end-987\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"19\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-89\" data-path-to-node=\"7,4,0\"><span class=\"citation-985 citation-986 citation-end-986\">Wild Photos {G. Only available online}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"20\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-985 citation-end-985\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"21\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container luminous-sources ng-star-inserted\"><button class=\"button multiple-button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details. Opens side panel.\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68244515d81e25b6-90\" data-path-to-node=\"7,5,0\"><span class=\"citation-983 citation-984 citation-end-984\">Photo Monthly {E. Advice about photography locations}<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"22\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-983 citation-end-983\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"23\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. Useful technical advice"}, {"optionText": "B. Easy to understand advice"}, {"optionText": "C. Free offers"}, {"optionText": "D. Reports about new products"}, {"optionText": "E. Advice about photography locations"}, {"optionText": "F. High quality photos"}, {"optionText": "G. Only available online"}, {"optionText": "H. Monthly competitions"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dc37ab7d-592d-4131-be28-1b5028162610', '18d88cc6-78d3-4e76-9481-8f27485e317b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17 and 18', '', '<p><span class="citation-979 citation-980">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-979 citation-980">TWO</span></strong><span class="citation-979 citation-980"> letters, </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="20"><span class="citation-979 citation-980">A-E</span></strong><span class="citation-979 citation-980 citation-end-980">.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="26"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-979 citation-end-979"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="27"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-977 citation-978">Which </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="31"><span class="citation-977 citation-978">TWO</span></strong><span class="citation-977 citation-978 citation-end-978"> useful features of the Photo Safari tour does John mention?<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="28"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-977 citation-end-977"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="29"><!----></sup></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A the photography classes"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B having space to store equipment"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C the high standard of accommodation"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D the quality of the food"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E the airport pick-up service"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('201bdd5b-d56d-4ba9-8709-631eeb7a7a00', '18d88cc6-78d3-4e76-9481-8f27485e317b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19 and 20', '', '<p><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-957">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-957">TWO</span></strong><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-957"> letters, </span><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="20"><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-957">A-E</span></strong><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-957 citation-end-957">.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="49"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-956 citation-end-956"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="50"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-954 citation-955 citation-end-955"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="51"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-954 citation-end-954"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="52"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-950 citation-951 citation-952 citation-953">Which </span><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="31"><span class="citation-950 citation-951 citation-952 citation-953">TWO</span></strong><span class="citation-950 citation-951 citation-952 citation-953 citation-end-953"> opinions does John give about his holiday with Photo Safari?<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="53"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-950 citation-951 citation-952 citation-end-952"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="54"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-950 citation-951 citation-end-951"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="55"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-950 citation-end-950"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="56"><!----></sup></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A Good advice was given about what clothes to take."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B There were photo opportunities every day."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C The non-photographers had a good time."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D It was the best time of year to see the animals."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E The guides knew a lot about photography."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b7289197-63fd-48d4-aadc-0c8bb0c74e7c', 'ed85474e-070c-4352-9aab-ce28ac90fcf3', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. asked a lot of questions"}, {"option_text": "B. misunderstood an explanation"}, {"option_text": "C. learned some new information"}], "question": "During the lecture about restoration and types of paint, Jenny"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. deciding the cause of damage to the portrait"}, {"option_text": "B. imagining what the restored portrait would look like"}, {"option_text": "C. choosing the best method for restoring the portrait"}], "question": "What do the students think will be the most difficult part of their assignment?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the visit was inspiring"}, {"option_text": "B. the restorer''s work was exhausting"}, {"option_text": "C. the subject matter of the picture was interesting"}], "question": "When discussing their trip to the restorer''s studio, the students agree that"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. feature local scenes"}, {"option_text": "B. are by well-known artists"}, {"option_text": "C. show famous people"}], "question": "Jenny thinks that the authorities give priority to restoring paintings which"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('480adf58-f06e-4b4e-b3fc-1546433f147a', '73b79239-1e2f-45b4-b0c3-348156a3b5f9', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25-26', '', '<p data-start="903" data-end="929">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="931" data-end="1021">Which <strong>TWO </strong>additions will Terence make to the part of the presentation on the sculptures?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. enlarged pictures of the sculptures"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. more material about the subjects"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. more about his personal opinion of the art works"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. extra information about the techniques used"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. additional information about the artists"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4c8768d7-de80-4cd0-a4b2-68f63cc75a81', 'd997ca98-1334-426e-b5e2-62ed98bec439', 'matching', 'Questions 21–26', NULL, '<p>What reason do teachers give for using each of the following picture books with children?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-I,</strong> next to questions <strong>21-26</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Picture books</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>I Spy Friends {I It features well-known characters.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Goodnight Little Rabbit {A The pictures show changing times of day.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Boat Party {E The pictures were done by a famous illustrator.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Puppy and Friends {F There is a surprise at the end of the story.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Hats and Socks {C It has an uncommon plot structure.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A Family Adventure {D The text can easily be turned into song.}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A The pictures show changing times of day."}, {"optionText": "B The words are fun to say out loud."}, {"optionText": "C It has an uncommon plot structure."}, {"optionText": "D The text can easily be turned into song."}, {"optionText": "E The pictures were done by a famous illustrator."}, {"optionText": "F There is a surprise at the end of the story."}, {"optionText": "G The pictures are simple line drawings."}, {"optionText": "H It was published very recently."}, {"optionText": "I It features well-known characters."}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\">PART 3: PICTURE BOOKS PRESENTATION</h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Hi, are you ready to discuss our presentation?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Yeah sure. So what are we going to say about teachers reading picture books with young children?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Hmm, I think we should start with the reasons why teachers use picture books. The journal article we read mentioned several picture books and why they&#8217;re popular with teachers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Right, like <em data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">I Spy Friends</em>. It&#8217;s a lovely story.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Yeah, the children like to find the familiar faces from the fairy tales they know so well, and they&#8217;re all doing predictable things. The article said children find this familiarity very comforting. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">(21) I (It is popular with boys/familiarity).</span></strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Yes, now how about <em data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">Goodnight Little Rabbit</em>, which has those delightful pictures? I love the way the colours get darker as the book progresses, indicating how evening turns into night.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Me too. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>The article said that’s why teachers like it—very cute and a good example of visual subtext. Hard to believe that it came out over 60 years ago; it&#8217;s still relevant. (22) A (It is too long)</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> I really liked what the article said about <em data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">The Boat Party</em>. There’s a lot of repetition, which I think would be great for vocabulary development.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> That&#8217;s true, but apparently it&#8217;s the images that make it popular with children. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">The artist is really well known and children often ask for her books. (23) E (It has won a prize).</span></strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Oh, that&#8217;s good to know. And shall we also include <em data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">Puppy and Friends</em>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Yes, it sounds like an innocent title, but the article warns that there&#8217;s a bit of a fright—you know, the one on the last page when the puppy suddenly encounters the scary cat. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>Teachers like to use this to help children explore their emotions. (24) F (The characters are very likable).</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Sounds good. <em data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">Hats and Socks</em> is a good one. It doesn&#8217;t really have a beginning and an end, does it? Which is unusual.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> That&#8217;s why teachers like this one though, because it&#8217;s so different. It&#8217;s good for children to hear a story that doesn&#8217;t follow the usual pattern. And the pages are so full of life and colour. <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"204\">(25) C</strong> (It is a good example of its type).</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> A good choice. Hmm, okay, and for our last one, how about <em data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">A Family Adventure</em>? This one uses a lot of the same language throughout, which I think can help with letter and word recognition.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong> Teachers say it has a really poetic feel to it; they often sing it to a simple tune. (26) D (The story is quite simple).</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Yes, and it&#8217;s full of beautiful watercolours too.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> In the next part of our presentation, shall we look at some of the other research? I really liked Smith&#8217;s article about the history of picture books.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Picture books haven&#8217;t been around for that long, of course, and as we know from our reading lists, there&#8217;s a lot of research on them already. Smith makes some interesting points.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Yes, one thing that shocked me was that some people don&#8217;t consider picture books as proper writing because they don&#8217;t have enough words in them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Yes, that was unexpected for me as well. I think they should be just as respected as other works of fiction. <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">(27/28) B (The argument that they are not literature).</span></strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Smith also mentioned that books from other countries are very popular here, even though they don&#8217;t show our daily life.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> I think that&#8217;s interesting, but it&#8217;s the same for adult fiction too—people want variety. What I didn&#8217;t realize is how fixed the number of pages is.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>Me neither. I wasn&#8217;t expecting that. They&#8217;re so strictly limited to 32 pages. It&#8217;s important, so let&#8217;s include it. (27/28) A (Their standard length).</strong></span></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Alright, now let&#8217;s think about other aspects of picture books we want to include in our presentation. How about the characters?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> Okay, well, a lot of them feature animals or families, often in very traditional roles. But do you think we need to talk about that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> For me, the main thing is that they are mostly printed as board books. The cardboard material makes it easy for young children to turn their pages.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>I agree, and it&#8217;s essential for children to hold books and learn how they open at the front and that the text goes in a certain direction. (29/30) A (The material they are made from).</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 1:</strong> Good point. Why don&#8217;t we also discuss how culture is important in picture books, like the importance of respecting the elderly?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student 2:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>Yes, it&#8217;s probably different all over the world. (29/30) D (Cultural elements in them).</strong></span></p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4da1269b-11cf-4f11-8b0b-183c3f4976e1', 'd997ca98-1334-426e-b5e2-62ed98bec439', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27–28', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> points from Smith’s article about picture books did both speakers find surprising?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "their standard length how recent the genre is", "correct": true}, {"option": "the argument that they are not literature", "correct": true}, {"option": "the lack of research about this age group", "correct": false}, {"option": "the popularity of books from overseas", "correct": false}, {"option": "the variety of versions", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e8f0a5f9-254c-4bb7-9cc9-166d4ea94fe2', 'ed85474e-070c-4352-9aab-ce28ac90fcf3', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p data-start="939" data-end="1011"><strong data-start="939" data-end="1011">What comment do the students make about each of the following books?</strong></p>
<p data-start="1013" data-end="1112">Choose <strong data-start="1020" data-end="1027">SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-start="1079" data-end="1086">A–H</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<h3 data-section-id=\"6xbvdo\" data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"470\">Books</h3>\n<p>25. Bringing Old Pictures Back to Life {C too basic to be of much use}</p>\n<p>26. Preserving Masterpieces {G focuses on historical aspects}</p>\n<p>27. Saving Paintings {F requires scientific knowledge}</p>\n<p>28. Approaches to Restoration {D deals with modern techniques}</p>\n<p>29. Art Conservation Today {B useful tips on preventing problems}</p>\n<p>30. Restoring Fine Art {A good visuals}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A good visuals"}, {"optionText": "B useful tips on preventing problems"}, {"optionText": "C too basic to be of much use"}, {"optionText": "D deals with modern techniques"}, {"optionText": "E rather out of date"}, {"optionText": "F requires scientific knowledge"}, {"optionText": "G focuses on historical aspects"}, {"optionText": "H wide international coverage"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7d66ba1f-d763-4dd7-b4ff-e480af686ce0', 'b031d9c4-5216-4775-9da7-482eb1d557ed', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Dormancy</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="0">Organisms enter dormancy to:</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="3">
<li>
<p>save available {Resources}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Value of dormancy</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="3,1,1">
<li>
<p>can live in conditions which are environmentally {stressful}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>can live in a lot of places</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>have less {competition} from other animals</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0">Causes of dormancy</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="5">
<li>
<p>temperature changes and {light} changes</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>food, water, oxygen</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Dormancy in insects</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p>They {experience} their metabolism during diapause</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Diapause occurs during extreme conditions</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">The African lungfish</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p>It buries itself in the {mud} to create a slimy cocoon</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Two dangers: {starvation} and desiccation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Snails</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p>Some close up with a membrane while dormant.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Light-coloured shells reflect sunlight and limit<strong> </strong>{evaporation}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">The Arctic ground squirrel</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p>Its hibernation occurs in insulated, underground {nest}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>40% weight loss</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>After waking up, the first part of the body to heat up is the {heart}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('30078aa4-a6ed-4ea5-8a14-7c3645e93bdc', 'abda3c23-0b52-4bae-a212-c9266748abfd', 'radio', 'Questions 21-25', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, or C.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "At first, it was unpopular with customers."}, {"content": "It has gained a lot of interest from chefs."}, {"content": "Many shops are using the idea now."}], "question": "According to Dominic, what is surprising about the supermarket garden project?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "The technology might not be well developed."}, {"content": "The cost could be too high."}, {"content": "There may not be enough room."}], "question": "What do the speakers identify as a possible problem with the solar carpark idea?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "they are much cheaper to build than was predicted."}, {"content": "animal populations become more genetically diverse."}, {"content": "they greatly reduce the number of car accidents."}], "question": "According to the speakers, the unexpected benefit of wildlife crossings is that"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "how many countries the movement has spread to"}, {"content": "how fast cities can convert to 100% renewable energy"}, {"content": "how much help is given to participating communities"}], "question": "What is impressive about the 100% renewable energy campaign?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "It helps businesses undertake eco-friendly projects."}, {"content": "It encourages people to buy sustainable products."}, {"content": "It creates a sense of community in the people who participate."}], "question": "What positive point about “carrot-mobbing” does Elia describe?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Part 3: </strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Okay everyone, get into pairs and look at the innovative environmental solutions we’ve been reading about this week. Discuss some of the pros and cons of each one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> You want to work together Ella?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> Sure Dominic. Which solution do you wanna look at first?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> I think the supermarket garden project’s interesting.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>Ella: </strong>That’s where the supermarket grows fruit and vegetables in the store and sells them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> Yes, understandably, only a few shops have decided to adopt this idea. It’s hard to set up.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Ella: </strong>What’s the reaction from customers?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> Well, of course they love the idea.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">(21) One thing I didn’t expect though was that the idea is hugely popular with local chefs [Answer: B]</strong></span></span>, and many of them are finding new ways to use the plants in all their different stages of growth.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> I see. I found the solar car park idea to be really practical.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> I know what you mean. Putting solar panels on the roofs of car parks to generate electricity might be a cost-effective way to power a whole shopping centre.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"6\">(22) The difficulty could be finding space to put all the panels [Answer: C]</strong></span>. Some smaller shopping centres probably don’t have covered car parks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> That’s right. It’s a shame because the technology seems to be all there and ready to go if the conditions are right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella: </strong>What do you think of the wildlife crossing solution? You know, when a bridge or a tunnel is built over or under a major roadway so that animals can cross.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> That idea has become very popular and has so many benefits. A lot of research has been done, hasn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> Yes. It’s not surprising that the data reveals a huge drop in the number of road accidents in areas where there are wildlife crossings. That’s one of the predicted outcomes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong>Dominic</strong>: Something I read about in the research, which I’d never considered before, was how the animal populations in these areas are affected. Naturally more of them survive, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"354\">(23) because their habitat is not interrupted too much by the roads, the genetic diversity of local species has improved [Answer: B]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> That’s true. It’s worth the huge cost of building them if the result is a win-win for people and animals. I found the 100% <strong>renewable energy campaign</strong>, like solar and wind energy, to be really impressive.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> Yes, it’s not so much the size of the movement—I mean only a few countries are involved—as <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">(24) the amount of support offered once a community joins [Answer: C]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong>Ella: </strong>Considering the sheer amount of time and planning it takes for a city to convert completely to renewables, the organizers of the movement would need to do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> Did you read about <strong>carrot mobbing</strong> as an environmental movement?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> What’s that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> It’s where huge numbers of people learn through the internet about where to shop at stores that use the profits to support environmental projects.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> So they stop buying products that aren’t eco-friendly? Like a boycott?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> No, actually it’s the opposite of that.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">(25) It allows businesses to fund initiatives to help protect the environment by boosting their profiles [Answer: A]</strong></span></span>. It’s a pity that most participants don’t get to know each other personally; it’s all through online notices.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Aerial Reforestation Process (Flow Chart)</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now everyone, let’s look at one particular environmental innovation: aerial reforestation. With your partner, discuss the process involved in this idea.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-2902\">Ella:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-2902 citation-end-2902\"> So aerial reforestation is where they drop mixtures from planes to sow vegetables, grains or trees and so on in areas that might be hard to reach.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span> Let’s see, what are the steps?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> Well, the first step is choosing the right area. Whatever size land you’re working on, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">(26) ensuring there’s enough light [H] is crucial</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> The next step, whatever you’re planting, is to make sure you have the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">(27) right seeds [C]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong>Dominic :</strong>To give them a better chance against the competition from other plants, you need to use a lot.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> So then you make a mixture with decent quality, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">(28) durable compost [E] for nourishment</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic :</strong> Then do they infuse it with insecticide?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> That’s not necessary in this model. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">The next step is pressing the whole thing into a small chunk of <strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">(29) clay [G] to make a ball</strong>.</span><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details for citation from Penn State University. Opens side panel.\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwibysXC1LWSAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQmgQ\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> This may then be covered in an outer material, such as paper,</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong>Dominic: </strong>right? <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">That way, when it lands, <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">(30) it will add balanced nutrients [D] to the mixture</strong></span>,</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong>Ella: </strong>Yes, and it may also protect it from insects and other plants.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dominic:</strong> Yes, and a few days before they release it from the plane onto the land below, the final step is dipping it in water just enough to get the germination process started.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ella:</strong> Yes, and after that…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c983c947-d2ea-4cec-9c18-1f3dd65f8560', 'd997ca98-1334-426e-b5e2-62ed98bec439', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29–30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> aspects of picture books do the speakers agree to talk about in their presentation?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "the material they are made from", "correct": true}, {"option": "common characters in them", "correct": false}, {"option": "the variety of roles in them", "correct": false}, {"option": "cultural elements in them", "correct": true}, {"option": "the future of the genre", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c7871380-b208-4132-a14b-107ecfa1584b', '915ffb65-0db5-4e50-b6a0-90f1694806cc', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<div class="instruction">
