<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;">in a motel</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 0%; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt;" valign="top" width="144">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;">went {snow boarding}</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 0%; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt;" valign="top" width="144">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;">book some less on in advance</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 1</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Hi Anna, how was your holiday to Jackson Island?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> It was good, there’s quite a lot to see. It’s quite a big island really.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Yeah, I was thinking of going in the summer. So where would you recommend going on the island?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Well, the capital of course, Camford. I stayed there with my cousin.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> What did you do there?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Well, actually I spent most of my time there shopping.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> So has it got good shopping centres?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes, but they’re the same as at home really. So I did all my shopping in the market, which is great.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Hmm, what kinds of things are good to buy there?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Everything, but bags and shoes especially. Just make sure you’ve got <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(1) cash</strong></span> with you, as most of the stalls don’t take credit cards.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> OK, that’s good to know. Where else did you go?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Well, my cousin and I went to Newtown. She said it was famous for its modern architecture. We only had half a day there, so we took a bus tour around the town. But if I were you, I’d give the bus tour a miss. Unless you know a lot about architecture, the buildings all look the same. There’s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(2) museum</strong></span> though, that’s supposed to be good. You might like that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Okay, I’ll give it a go then.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> After that, we headed for Golden Beach, because we were going to meet up with an old friend that I hadn’t seen for years. But we had to stay in a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(3) caravan</strong></span></span> as the hotels were all booked up.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Is it as pretty as it looks in the brochures?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes, it’s very picturesque. We did some <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(4) sailing</strong></span> on the most beautiful blue sea. It was so clear that you could see the bottom even quite far out to sea. That part of the trip was great, and I’d have liked to have stayed even longer. I’d suggest staying there for a minimum of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(5) 4 days</strong></span> if I were you. We had two days there and it wasn’t nearly enough.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Sounds great. I’ll put that on my “must do” list. Was that the end of your trip?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> No, after Golden Beach, we drove into the centre of the island to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(6) White Mountain</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> White as in the colour?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes! The island’s great because you can go from the beaches up to the snowy mountain in a couple of hours. We took a tent because we were going to camp, but the weather was so cold—in fact, it was snowing when I was there—that we stopped in a motel instead.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Did you go skiing then?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> No, but we tried <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(7) snowboarding</strong></span>, and it was harder than it looked. It looks so easy when you see other people doing it, but it took me ages to get the hang of it. I wish I’d had some lessons, but you had to make your bookings in advance.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> OK, I’ll look into that thanks.</p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\"></div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> So are there any other tips or advice you could give me?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> I don’t know, let me think… Oh, one place you should try to visit is this very quaint cafe which is at the foot of the mountain. It has the best <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(8) cakes</strong> </span>ever! It’s worth going there just for them.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Hmm, I’ll have to try those. So what other advice would you give?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Oh, let me think… uh… we didn’t really have any problems.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Well, how did you get around when you were there?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> We wanted to get a motorbike at first—they’re very cheap to hire and great fun to ride as the roads are very good. But it turned out not to be a good idea because the weather is so changeable. You’d be much better off in a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(9) car</strong></span>. There are plenty of places where you can hire them and the roads are well signposted so you won’t get lost.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> And presumably I can get a map when I get there?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Anna:</strong> Well you can, but they are expensive. It’d be better to get one—a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(10) map</strong></span>—here before you go.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>John:</strong> Great, that’s been really useful. Thank you!</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('251c26d6-5478-4213-92d6-f0cabf4162bd', '355d6413-493c-4247-a143-cf11b15c79e5', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–10', '<p data-start="685" data-end="774">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="685" data-end="774">Write <strong data-start="740" data-end="757">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="776" data-end="911"><strong data-start="776" data-end="791">More Advice</strong><br data-start="791" data-end="794">• Try the {cakes} at the cafe on the mountain.<br data-start="844" data-end="847">• Hire a {car}<br data-start="868" data-end="871">• Buy a {map} before the holiday.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9ee29ee5-6cbc-4efe-8f44-9a7c808ebb83', '910ae712-4030-4b05-9c88-c818e5593a57', 'matrix', 'Questions 11–15', '', '<p>Label the plan below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, A–H, next to questions 11–15.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="482" height="443" loading="lazy"></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Bike sheds ", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Snack shop ", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Fitness rooms ", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Family rooms ", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "TV room ", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>SECTION 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Bob Grain:</strong> Welcome to Gram Pic Arts Campus for our annual Residential Arts Weekend. I’m Bob Grain, director of the program. It’s a large campus, it’s quite easy to get lost, so I’m going to give you a quick overview of the most important places here.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Right, I’m glad you all found your way here to reception first. A word about parking: we do have a free temporary car park here. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">And for those of you coming by bike, the <strong>(11) bike sheds</strong> aren’t far from reception. You’ll see them on your left as you walk down South Lane towards the residential rooms <strong>(G)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, dinner is in the dining room at 7:30.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> If you need something to eat now, the <strong>(12) snack shop</strong> is still open. The quickest way to get there is to leave here, go straight through the office—they won’t mind—the ornamental ponds in front of you, and the snack shop is the building on your left <strong>(E)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The fitness facilities are even better this year. We’ve outgrown the old fitness rooms which were next to the office. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">To find the new <strong>(13) fitness rooms</strong> from here, walk up to North Road. They’re at the end in the last block, next to the dining room <strong>(A)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, your bedrooms are quite near. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">You can see the single rooms in the tall block to the far left of us across South Lane. Couples and families are in our <strong>(14) family rooms</strong> right next to them <strong>(F)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I’m afraid there aren’t any TVs in the rooms. We ask you to keep the noise down, please. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">We have a <strong>(15) TV room</strong>—you can probably see it from here—it’s right opposite us in the big red building <strong>(H)</strong>.</span></p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\"></div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Bob Grain:</strong> But there are gaps in our timetables for some extra options. You may have this information in your brochure, but there’ve been some changes.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Firstly, the <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>drama option</strong>.</span> I’m afraid our theatre and practice rooms here are being refurbished and are out of use. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">We decided against using our sports hall and instead we’re going to use our <strong>(16) lecture rooms</strong>, which we’ve converted into a theatre for the weekend <strong>(C)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There are also changes to the <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>photography option</strong></span> this year. This option isn’t open to everyone. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">We decided for practical reasons to reserve it for <strong>(17) beginners with no previous experience (A: people new to photography)</strong>. </span></span>Let me remind you that you don’t need any special equipment, that’s provided. The tutors have said that unfortunately, they can’t accept parents with children because that proved too disruptive last time. But if you’re over 18, that’s fine.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">On to the<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <strong>writing option</strong>.</span> Previous courses looked at starting your novel. This year we wondered about focusing on the techniques of writing different types of poetry. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">However, as a result of many requests, we’ve decided the workshop will concentrate on helping each participant write one or more <strong>(18) short stories (B)</strong>.</span> Poetry, maybe some future time.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>music</strong></span>. The brochure says you’ll go to a concert—that’s a misprint. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">Instead, you’ll be writing and <strong>(19) putting on your own performance (C: giving a performance)</strong>, a concert for yourselves.</span></span> Unfortunately, the singing tutor is ill. It’s too late to replace her, so we’ve had to cancel singing lessons. Apologies for that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Finally, the <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>crèche</strong></span>. This is available for all families on the program and there are still some places left.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> I’m sure you’ll be pleased to know that <strong>(20) the charge for this hasn’t increased since last year (A: it costs the same as last year)</strong>. </span>Lunch is included, but of course parents are welcome to collect their children and spend the lunch break with them. May I remind you that any fees for this service must be settled in full at the end of the last day.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">So, has anybody got any questions?</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('80a0e638-61c3-4510-8434-1c818f162ac4', '910ae712-4030-4b05-9c88-c818e5593a57', 'radio', 'Questions 16–20', '', '<p data-start="50" data-end="112">Choose the correct letter <strong data-start="98" data-end="111">A, B or C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "in the theatre"}, {"option_text": "in the sports hall"}, {"option_text": "in the lecture rooms"}], "question": "The drama option takes place"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "people new to photography."}, {"option_text": "people with special equipment."}, {"option_text": "parents and children."}], "question": "The photography option is reserved for"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "poetry techniques."}, {"option_text": "short stories."}, {"option_text": "starting a novel."}], "question": "The writing option will focus on"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "singing classes."}, {"option_text": "going to a concert."}, {"option_text": "giving a performance."}], "question": "The music option involves"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "the costs the same as last year."}, {"option_text": "lunch costs extra."}, {"option_text": "parents must pay in advance."}], "question": "What information is given about the creche?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0287c870-5850-475a-9221-fd44e415b6e5', '73b79239-1e2f-45b4-b0c3-348156a3b5f9', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Presentation on African art</strong></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. He read several journal articles."}, {"option_text": "B. He attended an exhibition."}, {"option_text": "C. He spent some time in Nigeria."}], "question": "What first attracted Terence to the topic of Ife sculptures?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. abstract designs."}, {"option_text": "B. fish and wild animals."}, {"option_text": "C. people."}], "question": "In his presentation Terence will focus on sculptures featuring"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. He received money from an arts organisation."}, {"option_text": "B. His mother and father paid for him."}, {"option_text": "C. He wrote about the trip for a newspaper."}], "question": "How did Terence finance his trip to Ife?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. helping at an archaeological site"}, {"option_text": "B. the professor he met"}, {"option_text": "C. the artists he got to know"}], "question": "What was most memorable for Terence about his trip?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"67\" data-end=\"235\">Tutor: Okay Terence, now I’ve looked through your preliminary outline and notes for the presentation on the art of the Ife region in Africa – that’s in Nigeria right?</p>\n<p data-start=\"237\" data-end=\"324\">Terence: Yes, I’m concentrating on life sculptures from the 12th to the 15th century.</p>\n<p data-start=\"326\" data-end=\"455\">Tutor: How did you get interested in that? I know there have been some recent articles in the journals about African sculpture.</p>\n<p data-start=\"457\" data-end=\"748\">Terence: Well I’ve read most of those now, but <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(21) initially I got my introduction to this at a special display at the City Museum a few years ago</span></strong>. I just happened to be there and saw these works and thought they were fantastic, and I even went to Nigeria last summer to see more of them.</p>\n<p data-start=\"750\" data-end=\"894\">Tutor: I’ve seen the photos for your presentation and I must say the sculptures are gorgeous portrayals of what appear to be kings and Queens.</p>\n<p data-start=\"896\" data-end=\"1249\">Terence: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(22) Yes I decided to concentrate on those as they’re the most typical</strong></span>. They’re interesting because they’re so naturalistic, unlike the abstract figures we often associate with African art. There’s also a lovely sculpture of a mudfish and one of the scaly crocodile, but I didn’t get very good pictures of those so I won’t spend long on them.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1251\" data-end=\"1361\">Tutor: Right. So what was the city of Ife like when these works were made? It’s on the Niger River isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1363\" data-end=\"1523\">Terence: Yeah, the boat traffic’s what made it a center of commerce then as it still is today, but nowadays it’s better known as the home of a big university.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1525\" data-end=\"1587\">Tutor: Speaking of modern day life, tell me about your trip.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1589\" data-end=\"1951\">Terence: Ha, I was incredibly lucky to be able to get enough money to go. My parents encouraged me but they couldn’t afford to send me. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23) I applied for a grant from the Arts Council and in the end I got it</strong></span>. I also wrote a series of articles about my trip for the local newspaper but I didn’t get any money for that. I was just pleased to get them published.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1953\" data-end=\"1992\">Tutor: And the highlight of the trip?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1994\" data-end=\"2350\">Terence: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(24) That had to be meeting a professor working on the site in Ife</strong></span> who had been a young boy when they first discovered the sculptures by accident at a building site in 1938. He had been working at the site, of course I also got to talk to lots of artists who are working there today, and I got to try my hand at making a little sculpture myself.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2352\" data-end=\"2355\">\n<p data-start=\"2357\" data-end=\"2488\">Tutor: Well let’s see what you might do to improve what you’re planning for your presentation. About the sculptures themselves…</p>\n<p data-start=\"2490\" data-end=\"2708\">Terence: I think <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(25/26) I need to add as much as possible about the details of the way they were made</strong></span>. Of course, I can’t add anything about the artists who made them because nobody really knows anything about them.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2710\" data-end=\"2937\">Tutor: All good points, and you’ve certainly said enough about what the sculptures depict and what the subjects are, that’s well covered. But <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(25/26) I’d make some bigger photos of them so you can clearly see the fine detail</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2939\" data-end=\"3175\">Terence: Okay, and I would limit my personal reactions to these works of art if I were you. I know you think they’re fantastic. You’re right, I’ll contain my enthusiasm. What about the section of the presentation which I call history?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3177\" data-end=\"3349\">Terence: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27/28) I’d like to go into more depth about the history of that whole area, you know in the countries around Nigeria</strong></span>. That would make the presentation stronger.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3351\" data-end=\"3664\">Tutor: But I think you’ve covered the situation regarding the rulers of the country quite well and you’ve got plenty already about what the Ife people were doing then and the way their society was structured. And in fact I think you could cut out the bit about modern Nigerian history because it’s not relevant.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3666\" data-end=\"3853\">Terence: I agree that doesn’t fit, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27/28) but perhaps I should concentrate more on the religious beliefs</strong></span>, since all these sculptures do seem to have some kind of religious association.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3855\" data-end=\"4092\">Tutor: Good, I can lend you a book on that. Now, probably the part the class will find most interesting is the report of your trip to Nigeria and the research you did there. So I gather you managed to use the university library in Ife?</p>\n<p data-start=\"4094\" data-end=\"4547\">Terence: Yes, as soon as I had explained why I wanted the information, that was no problem; they couldn’t have been more helpful. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29/30) There were some interesting accounts of how the first sculptures were found and what happened to them, which I want to include</strong></span>. What struck me when I saw the sculptures in Nigeria is the extent to which 20th century European artists were influenced by them, but that’s beyond the scope of my presentation I think.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4549\" data-end=\"4646\">Tutor: Yes. What about the sources of the materials they used? You don’t mention that anywhere.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4648\" data-end=\"4888\">Terence: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29/30) I didn’t manage to find out much about that</strong></span>. I want to cover <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29/30) the theories about who the original sculptors were though</strong></span>… the idea that a lot of them may have been made by the same person. That’s very interesting.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4890\" data-end=\"4982\">Tutor: It is, isn’t it? Right, well thanks for all the advice. Now I think I need to work.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cf96e302-9825-49e8-a0c2-0f62eb51ab88', 'f9d004dc-8cd9-4f59-9920-4c90c0c4c470', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20–23) and the list of researchers below. Match each statement with the correct researcher, A–E.</p>
<p><strong>NB You may use any letter more than once.</strong></p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of researchers", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Edward M Hallowell", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Paul E Dux", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "David Strayer", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Etienne Koechlin", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Keith Laws", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Questions 20–23: Matching Researchers</strong></h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s: C (David Strayer)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “David Strayer’s research… ‘super-taskers’ exhibit <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">different patterns of brain activity</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task: C (David Strayer)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> “Strayer’s research shows… <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">more mistakes are made</strong> and it takes longer to complete each activity.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task: A (Edward M Hallowell)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> “Edward M Hallowell even describes multi-tasking as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">‘mythical activity’</strong> in which people believe they can perform…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action: E (Keith Laws)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> “…men tend to jump to it… ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">It’s as if they don’t stop to reflect and plan for a moment</strong>,’ says Professor Keith Laws.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('41ce95dc-ba5c-4145-82fd-b2c24c50b374', 'f9d004dc-8cd9-4f59-9920-4c90c0c4c470', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the summary below. Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Super-taskers</strong></span></p>
<p>Super-taskers are those of us who possess special multi-tasking ability. They can be found in all professions. People who are pilots, chefs and doctors are often super-taskers, and super-taskers are most likely to achieve a {position} that is high on the career ladder. Super-taskers typically have to undertake many tasks simultaneously that need their {attention}. Genes play an important role in having this capability; these people have a special brain {structure} which helps them do what we cannot.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Questions 24–26: Summary Completion</strong></h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. position</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “…super-taskers will rise to a top <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">position</strong> in any occupation…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người siêu đa nhiệm thường đạt được vị trí cao trong sự nghiệp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. attention</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “…juggling various tasks that demand <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">attention</strong> at the same time.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Công việc của họ đòi hỏi phải làm nhiều việc cần sự tập trung cùng lúc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. structure</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> “You are either born with the neural <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">structure</strong> that allows you to overcome…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khả năng này bắt nguồn từ cấu trúc não bộ đặc biệt mà họ có từ khi sinh ra.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e9a6215a-8ca6-449a-a011-f64993074c06', '73b79239-1e2f-45b4-b0c3-348156a3b5f9', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29-30', '', '<p data-start="1671" data-end="1697">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1699" data-end="1788">Which <strong>TWO </strong>features of his research in Nigeria will Terence discuss in his presentation?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. the influence of the sculptures on western artists"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B. the uncertainty over who made the sculptures"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. the sources of the materials used for the sculptures"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. the problems he faced in collecting information"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. the original discovery of the sculptures"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1e2a21f2-2125-44f2-831b-12d4df39ddbd', '716756ee-6214-46a5-aa78-b57613eccd18', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="105" data-end="173">Complete the notes below.<br data-start="130" data-end="133">Write <strong data-start="139" data-end="156">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3 data-start="180" data-end="203"><strong data-start="184" data-end="203">Photic sneezing</strong></h3>
<p data-start="205" data-end="338"><strong data-start="205" data-end="219">Background</strong><br data-start="219" data-end="222">Some people react to sunlight by:<br data-start="255" data-end="258">• a prickle in the nose       |<br data-start="281" data-end="284">• faster {breathing}            |⇒ relieved by a sneeze<br data-start="320" data-end="323">• watery eyes                    |</p>
<p data-start="340" data-end="426">This ‘photic’ sneeze cannot be controlled and is a {common} reflex.</p>
<p data-start="428" data-end="719"><strong data-start="428" data-end="451">Sneezing in general</strong><br data-start="451" data-end="454">• A sneeze is caused by some kind of irritation in the nose.<br data-start="514" data-end="517">• Nerve endings in the {face} are stimulated, leading to an explosion of air.<br data-start="615" data-end="618">• It is coordinated by the same mechanism that controls the production of {tears}</p>
<p data-start="721" data-end="1025"><strong data-start="721" data-end="754">Research into photic sneezing</strong><br data-start="754" data-end="757">The condition has been known for thousands of years.<br data-start="809" data-end="812">Aristotle: Why does the sun cause sneezing while a {fire} does not?<br data-start="900" data-end="903">Bacon showed the cause was light.<br data-start="936" data-end="939">Everett found 80% of photic sneezers shared the habit with {relatives}</p>
<p data-start="1027" data-end="1257"><strong data-start="1027" data-end="1041">Indicators<br></strong>Photic sneezers usually produce the same {number} of sneezes.<br data-start="1124" data-end="1127">The reaction is caused by a {contrast} in brightness.<br data-start="1197" data-end="1200">The sneeze takes {time} to recharge.</p>
<p data-start="1259" data-end="1461"><strong data-start="1259" data-end="1274">Application</strong><br data-start="1274" data-end="1277">The condition was often ignored apart from some research on photic sneezing among {pilots}<br data-start="1386" data-end="1389">But studying it may result in breakthroughs for more serious conditions.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 4: </strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Welcome to this lecture in the health sciences, intended to inspire you and get you thinking about your research project. Today, I want to show you how even ordinary human behavior like sneezing, which normally happens when you get a cold, may be worth studying.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Have you ever been walking outside when a bright shaft of sunlight hits you between the eyes? The reaction of some people is immediate: an unpleasant prickling in the nose, an increase in their <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(31) breathing</strong></span></span> rate, and an uncontrollable watering of the eyes. Then, almost as quickly, they sneeze and gain relief. This may happen every time they go into the sun. This so-called “photic” or light sneeze is a reflex, which means it can’t be controlled, and it’s very <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(32) common</strong></span></span>—anything between one in ten and one in three people might be affected.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In fact, a sneeze is triggered by an irritation of some sort in the linings of the nostrils. The result is a cascade of reactions, beginning with the stimulation of the nerve endings all over the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(33) face</strong></span> and generating an explosive expulsion of air at up to 95 miles an hour, like an extremely localized personal hurricane. The body’s coordination of such reactions is complicated and belongs to the subconscious control hardware that regulates other things—for example, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(34) tears</strong></span> in the eyes.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">People have been interested in the phenomenon of photic sneezing for thousands of years. The Greek philosopher Aristotle asked why the sun prompted us to sneeze, whereas th<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">e heat </span>of a <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">(35) </span></strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">fire</span> </strong></span>does not. A partial answer came 2,000 years later when the English philosopher Francis Bacon showed that his photic sneeze had nothing to do with heat. If he closed his eyes when going into the sun, he didn’t sneeze, even though the heat was still there.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Henry Everett, a consultant psychiatrist at Johns Hopkins University Hospital in Baltimore, was the first to make a systematic attempt to understand the condition, noting in 1964 that 30% of the staff employed in the Medical Department were photic sneezers. Everett did some further investigation; he found that while 80% of sneezers reported other sneezers among their <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(36) relatives</strong></span>, only 20% of non-sneezers did.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, there are factors that are certain indicators of a photic sneeze. First of all, those with the condition almost always sneeze a set <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">(<strong>37)</strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> </span>number</strong></span> of <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">times </span>on exposure to light. In addition to this, the sneeze depends on a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(38) contrast</strong></span></span> in visible brightness, such as when the sun moves out from behind a cloud. And the sneezing fit won’t be repeated immediately—the body needs <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(39) time</strong></span> before it can be recharged. So, if you go back into a darkened space and then immediately re-enter bright light, you will not sneeze again.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, on to possible applications of research in this area. The photic sneeze had long been overlooked because its effects are generally less than serious, although the government did once study it as a risk factor for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(40) pilots</strong>.</span> Yet, work on such a simple disorder might lead to important discoveries on more acute conditions, such as migraine or epilepsy, which are also caused by “crossed wires” in the nervous system. That is why I encourage you to select something similar for your first investigative medical project. It could be the beginning of something even more useful.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, let’s talk about the project timetable…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7aa81d88-de7c-4ebe-9d75-6e5d6177d4a1', 'a63d3da7-d010-48c8-9791-1ef2d1b9d3a8', 'fillup', 'Questions 6–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p><strong>February 1861: Storm warning service</strong><br>• FitzRoy received weather reports produced by ships using reliable {instruments}<br>• simultaneous weather reports were taken daily<br>• storm warnings were telegraphed to  {ports }  along the shore<br>• signals for ships were displayed using raised { flags  }<br>• the storm warning service was the greatest development in sea safety since the  {lifeboat}   was introduced</p>
<p><strong>August 1861: Public weather forecasting service</strong><br>• very popular in The Times newspaper<br>• frequently used by the English Queen for safe trips to a favourite { island  }<br>• FitzRoy’s forecasts were popular with fishermen but not with boat  {owners}<br>• in modern times FitzRoy’s  {name}   is used for a marine area<br>• FitzRoy produced a  {book }  which was respected by the scientific community</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c8df895a-0b86-447b-9d39-5ef8f61d172d', '88be8000-da6b-4b86-bc8d-f2fb02f4a6c6', 'radio', 'Questions 11–14', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
<p><strong>Sports Information for Parents</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the overall interest in sport has grown."}, {"content": "certain parents have given up these roles."}, {"content": "new types of sport are being introduced."}], "question": "The school is looking for new team coaches and managers because"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "confidence about the rules of a particular sport"}, {"content": "the ability to make children enthusiastic about a sport"}, {"content": "commitment to training the team for a full season"}], "question": "What does the speaker say is the most important thing a coach needs?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "attend an upcoming registration event."}, {"content": "can commit to two coaching sessions per week."}, {"content": "have their own child in the team."}], "question": "For parents who would like to coach rugby, one requirement is that they"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "pay a deposit at school."}, {"content": "ask the team manager for one."}, {"content": "visit the recommended local sports store."}], "question": "In order to get a netball uniform, parents will need to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 2</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Assistant Principal:</strong> Good evening parents, and thank you for offering your help. I’m here to talk about the sports programs that the children are taking part in this term. Although we do do sport during class time, children often have extra activities before or after school or at weekends, and that’s when we need you.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">First up, we’re looking for parents who would like to become team coaches or managers. We had some excellent people last year, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(11) some of those parents now have other commitments (B: given up these roles)</strong>.</span> It’s the Year 4 netball team, the Year 5 and 6 rugby teams, and the Year 3 hockey team that need new people.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now coaching, I know some parents might not be completely familiar with, say, rugby or netball rules, but don’t let that put you off. Obviously knowledge of the game helps, but if you’re keen, there are some coaching courses you can take before the training sessions for players begin ,and these also get held throughout the whole season. What’s really required is the right attitude. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(12) Are you the kind of person that can motivate kids and make the game seem exciting? (B: ability to make children enthusiastic)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">All the rugby training and matches are organised by North Shore Rugby Club. If you do volunteer to become a rugby coach, you’ll need to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(13) go along to an important day that’s coming up—that’s on Saturday the 23rd (A: attend upcoming registration event)</strong>.</span> It takes place on the rugby grounds and it’s when all the kids put their names down for a team, and the organisers are on hand to give parents a bit more information. Matches are on Saturday morning and training sessions on a Wednesday after school.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Moving on to netball matches and uniforms. Matches are on Monday at 4:00 PM. And for uniforms, we’ve just ordered a new set from the sports store in town, and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(14) parents must hire one from the school secretary for $15, which gets refunded at the end of the season (A: pay a deposit at school)</strong>.</span></p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\"></div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Assistant Principal:</strong> Okay, some of you are kindly helping with the cross-country running event. Children in years 3 to 6 will be running from school at the bottom of your map there. The route isn&#8217;t marked on your map.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I&#8217;m afraid, but I&#8217;m going to point out some different places that need parent supervision.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">(15) drink station is one. If you’re handing out water, head to the north car park and the station will be set up on the other side of the road from it, right by the flag post (C).</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Two or three parents will be needed to help out at the major <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(16) crossing point</strong>,</span> just to make sure everybody’s going the right way. So on the map, there’s that little footpath going up past the school, then it splits into three directions.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>The crossing point is at the end of the left-hand path heading west, just before you cross Summer Street (H)</strong>.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now we’ll need a couple of parents at the <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\">(17) halfway point</span></span></strong> to send the children in the right direction. So there are four buildings on the far left-hand side. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>The halfway point is just to the right of these buildings (B)</strong>.</span><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> Just cheer the kids on, and if anyone has given up running, that&#8217;s fine.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Okay, the teacher at our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(18) first aid</strong></span> post might need help sticking plasters on. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">The quickest way to get to first aid is to head up the footpath next to school and when you get to the second turning on the right, head down there and it’s sort of opposite the satellite dish (F).</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">What else? <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The (19) rest area is for children needing a break, and that’s the place nearest the south car park, near the road (G).</span></strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">And if any parent here is handy with a video camera, we’d really appreciate some help with filming the event. For the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(20) filming area</strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>, this means heading up the footpath by the school, then keep going up with the flag post on your left and the satellite dish on your right, and the filming spot is just there, in front of the trees (D).</strong></span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Well, I think that covers everything…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5ebffea8-b62d-4513-81a2-7316c3e81314', '88be8000-da6b-4b86-bc8d-f2fb02f4a6c6', 'matrix', 'Questions 15–20', NULL, '<p>Label the map below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, A–I, next to questions 15–20.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="553" height="402" loading="lazy"></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Drinks station", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Crossing point", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "Halfway point", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "First aid", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Rest area", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Filming area", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5b7b4a9f-a9b5-47a6-99b0-e8f7871a1506', '6789a48e-e46d-4248-be2a-a677ef191780', 'matching', 'Questions 21–25', NULL, '<p>What are the characteristics of the following analysis methods?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FIVE</strong> letters from the box next to questions 21-25</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Analysis methods </strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>PEST {C it does not fit our company}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Drill Down {D it will take too long}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>PMI {E it is easy to use}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Pareto {A it will save a lot of business time and effort}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>SWOT {G it is suitable to almost all sized companies}</p>\n<p> </p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A it will save a lot of business time and effort"}, {"optionText": "B it is visualized"}, {"optionText": "C it does not fit our company"}, {"optionText": "D it will take too long"}, {"optionText": "E it is easy to use"}, {"optionText": "F it is difficult to apply"}, {"optionText": "G it is suitable to almost all sized companies"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "PEST", "correctAnswer": "C it does not fit our company", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Drill Down", "correctAnswer": "D it will take too long", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "PMI", "correctAnswer": "E it is easy to use", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Pareto", "correctAnswer": "A it will save a lot of business time and effort", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "SWOT", "correctAnswer": "G it is suitable to almost all sized companies", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 3</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> Hi Francis, Sam. So, how did you go with applying the different theoretical business tools for the report I asked you to write?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> It was interesting and made us really focus on which tool was best to use when analysing a business.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> Good. So tell me what you found out.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam: </strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">We liked the theory behind <strong>PEST </strong>analysis—that’s Political, Economic, Social and Technological—although we’re </span></span><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong>(21)</strong></span> not sure if it was very applicable to our case. Some of the other groups had studies for which it worked really well and they said it was easy to use.</span><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span></strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>But I felt it focused too much on the big picture and was unsuitable for our company (C)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> I agree. On the other hand?<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> I enjoyed using the <strong>Drill Down</strong> method. It was painstaking to do and <strong>(22) we seemed to be working on it for ages (D: take too long)</strong>, but the results were worth waiting for.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam:</strong> Yes, I liked the way it eventually broke down complex problems.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> Yes, <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">I much prefer doing the <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>PMI</strong> </span>analysis. It was so straightforward to break down into its three components: Plus, Minus and Interesting implications.</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> You just needed to brainstorm these components and then write them up—fast and effective. And it didn&#8217;t make your brain hurt doing it. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Sam:</span></strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong> (23) I agree, and you don&#8217;t need any special training at all—anyone can use it. (E: easy to use)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> I agree. So, was there any tool that you thought was superior to the others?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam:</strong> In my opinion, the one tool that is critical to business, especially for larger companies, is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>Pareto</strong></span></span> analysis. If they apply Pareto analysis, they would see that by focusing on the critical 20% of their problems, they could generate 80% of the benefits. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(24) This would allow them to work faster and it also reduces their workload (A: save time and effort)</strong>.</span><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">It&#8217;s all about finding out what their basic problems are.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> I agree with Francis about Pareto, but my favourite was the <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>SWOT</strong> </span>analysis—you know, looking at the company’s Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities and Threats. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">It can be used in so many different situations; (25) it works in large and small companies and even down to departmental level (G: suitable to almost all sized companies).</span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\"></div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> Okay, I’ve read your draft report, but can you tell me a bit more about that company you focused on?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam:</strong> Well, the company we used in our study was a manufacturing company who have relied on distributors to take their product to the end user. We did some analysis examining the possibility of them distributing their own products.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis: </strong>We initially looked at their strengths. The company, although it is small, is well known and has a very good reputation. The management are very committed to increasing the company profits and they are confident this move would be successful.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam</strong>: Right, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong>and the company has quite a lot of staff who have previously worked for distribution companies, so the knowledge is already there (B: experienced employees).</strong></span> That was something we didn&#8217;t expect to find, and is probably going to help them the most to achieve their goals.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> I was quite impressed by some of the opportunities you detailed. I did think you missed something quite pertinent to their future growth, however.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> What was that?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(27) You didn’t consider the potential for establishing an offshore division (B: set up an overseas office)</strong>.</span></span>You talked about the company negotiating better terms with its suppliers—most of these are based abroad—and so if the company had a way of actually distributing the product there, this could be a tremendous opportunity and give them an edge over their competitors. </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Francis:</strong> That’s a good point. So what did you think about the threats we identified?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> I thought you did a good job. <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">I was really pleased to see that you considered how the (28) government’s planned environmental policy could really affect the viability of this venture… with this law being introduced next year (C: new legislation). </span></strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">they might need to find new ways of using their existing technology. </span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">It&#8217;s easy to identify what your competitors are doing, but it&#8217;s the bigger picture that often gets ignored. So Sam, what did you learn from this assignment?</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sam:</strong> Heaps, I guess. I hadn&#8217;t realized how much time it takes to ensure your company survives and profits. .<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> It was great to study the different tools in books, but (29) applying them in the real world was much harder than I thought (C: gap between reality and theory).</span></strong></span> It was a great learning experience. </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Professor:</strong> I&#8217;m glad I could make your assignment relevant. I’m basically happy with your report. You’ve got the format correct with the necessary headings, etcetera, and you&#8217;ve got sufficient details under the different headings.<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"> Just remember to (30) state whether or not you think the company should go ahead with the new venture (A: give a final determination). </span></strong>But you’ve done a good job so far.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5fcdf681-5c4a-4146-bbad-f9a1ae6b5702', '6789a48e-e46d-4248-be2a-a677ef191780', 'radio', 'Questions 26–30', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "reputation"}, {"content": "experienced employees"}, {"content": "management"}], "question": "What does Frances consider as the best strength of the company?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "seek for cheaper suppliers"}, {"content": "set up an overseas office"}, {"content": "compete with major competitors"}], "question": "What factor did Sam overlooked for the future growth of the company?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "increasing competition"}, {"content": "outdated technology"}, {"content": "new legislation"}], "question": "Which of the following can be the threat to a company?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "using better tools"}, {"content": "cost of a success business"}, {"content": "gap between reality and theory"}], "question": "What has Sam learned from the research?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "give a final determination"}, {"content": "reorganize a clear structure"}, {"content": "add more detailed information"}], "question": "What is the professor’s suggestion for the report?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4e2ffdbb-b8c8-4e8c-ae01-60a15cd21b1c', '00b8412f-8ebf-4cc9-aefe-a3c65e364c40', 'fillup', 'Questions 31 - 40', '<p>Complete the notes below,</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-start="92" data-end="115">Economics and Trust</strong></span></p>
<p>Trust relies on the stranger’s {kindness}</p>
<p>The understanding of trust can reduce {poverty}</p>
<p><strong data-start="215" data-end="239">How to measure trust</strong></p>
<p>• People’s ability of recognizing a person’s {face}</p>
<p>• Oxytocin will be released when {interaction} occurs</p>
<p><strong data-start="356" data-end="389">Experiments: two participants</strong></p>
<p>• The first participant decides whether to lend the money or not.</p>
<p>• The second participant has no {obligation} to return the money.</p>
<p>• Trust involves a {process}, so it is conditional.</p>
<p>• If animals have {cooperation}, they will be seen to have oxytocin.</p>
<p><strong data-start="654" data-end="675">Nash equilibrium:</strong></p>
<p>• Participants have no {expectations} that the other person would change his or her decision.</p>
<p>• People under stress have {high} levels of oxytocin.</p>
<p>• Oxytocin is a social {glue}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 4</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Lecturer:</strong> The development of trust is an essential social tool, allowing people to form productive and meaningful relationships, both at a professional and personal level. Trust is indispensable in friendship, love, families, and organizations, and plays a key role in economic exchange and politics.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Much recent evidence indicates that trust contributes to economic, political, and social success. When we make contacts with strangers, such as doing business with the clients who we meet for the first time, our trust in them can only rely on their <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(31) kindness</strong></span>. So from our own judgment or the comments from other people, we can have a rough idea if the stranger is trustworthy.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Trust is important because it is the basis around which all human relationships evolve. Without trust, there can be no relationship. Trust can come naturally or it can be manifested. If you find trust of this magnitude in life, then you are lucky. Also, you can always count on them to protect through all, if not most of life&#8217;s perils.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Trust is important because if you don&#8217;t trust someone, then they are not available.Believe it or not, reducing the chance of suffering from <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(32) poverty</strong></span> is to understand trust, because when you trust other people, you can have more support and resources.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>However, our ability </strong>to trust others varies from individual to individual, just like different people’s ability of recognizing a person’s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(33) face</strong></span> is not the same. Bonds of trust are also extremely fragile.A single act of betrayal, such as a marital affair, can instantly erase years of trustworthy behaviour. The consequences of such breaches in confidence can be disastrous and not only for a relationship.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The study demonstrates how oxytocin can facilitate social interactions after trust has been violated by potentially lowering defense mechanisms associated with social risks, and by overcoming negative feedback that is important for adapting behavior in the future. Luckily, oxytocin in our body has the ability to inspire trust in and among people. This chemical is released whenever <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(34) interaction</strong></span> happens between people.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To study social interactions, economists and more recently neuroscientists take advantage of a simple experiment. Two participants play the so-called “trust game”. The first participant is faced with the decision to keep a sum of money or share it with the second participant, who has no <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(35) obligation</strong></span> to give the money back. He would get more money if the second person returns it.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In this game, the first person is left with an important social dilemma: to trust or not to trust.Although it is more profitable to trust, doing so leaves the investor at risk of betrayal.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Trust is not something that naturally occurs when two people meet for the first time. It involves a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(36) process</strong>.</span> One person has to show the quality of being trustworthy to the other person. This can be achieved by certain behaviours and communication; therefore, trust is conditional. People should not take it for granted</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Oxytocin does not only exist in human beings; animals also have this gift, and it can be seen when they have <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(37) cooperation</strong></span> with each other. Oxytocin in monkeys, for example, allows them to work together to find food and to fight against enemies.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Nash equilibrium’s game theory: the first participant will make the best decision he can with no <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong>(38) expectations</strong></span> that the second participant would change his decision. The second participant will do the same, so the outcome depends on the decision of the other person. This game is similar to the one we just talked about.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The oxytocin level doesn’t stay the same in a person’s body. Studies have found that people who are under a lot of stress would have <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(39) high</strong></span> levels of oxytocin. Oxytocin causes a substantial increase in trust among humans, thereby greatly increasing the benefits from social interactions.It&#8217;s also noted that the effect of oxytocin on trust is not due to a general increase in the readiness to bear risks.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">On the contrary, oxytocin specifically affects an individual&#8217;s willingness to accept social risks arising through interpersonal interactions</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To sum up, oxytocin is like a kind of social <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(40) glue</strong> </span>that is helpful in social bonding. Further research is needed to explore oxytocin and trust and how this hormone can be used to strengthen our trust in others and even treat mental disorders that specifically relate to deficiencies in social behavior.</p>\n<p>Next we&#8217;re going to talk about&#8230;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bd5468a3-f8cd-4452-98f3-fe9d1e9f3afb', 'ccc02ffb-54d6-4fcd-93ce-7f4e88c3107f', 'matching', 'Questions 14-19', '', '<p>The text has <strong>six </strong>paragraphs. Choose the correct heading for each paragraph and move it into the gap.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Evidence that man’s ancestors had a concept of the future"}, {"optionText": "ii Research into the relation between brain size and memory"}, {"optionText": "iii Animals that can remember places and time"}, {"optionText": "iv Research into various animals’ capacity for future planning"}, {"optionText": "v A memory type described with reference to brain damage"}, {"optionText": "vi Conflicting experimental results concerning animal memory"}, {"optionText": "vii Research evidence of memory loss in various animals"}, {"optionText": "viii Experimental evidence of a relation between past and future in human mental processes"}, {"optionText": "ix Research into ways to improve episodic memory"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('25509a2c-3d7d-4c73-bba5-be3b06becde1', 'ccc02ffb-54d6-4fcd-93ce-7f4e88c3107f', 'checkbox', 'Questions 20–21', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>of the following statements concerning episodic memory are found in the text?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "Dr Tulving believes that most kinds of memory involve aspects of episodic memories"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "The experimental subject KC was unable to recall the process by which he learned to play a particular board game"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "In the case of KC, the subject’s episodic memory was affected by his brain injuries"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Dr Tulving carried out extensive observations of the episodic memories of animals as well as humans"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "To test his episodic memory, KC was given various mathematical problems to solve"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5d6cda3b-88c8-48ab-9677-2af2e3dba0dc', 'ccc02ffb-54d6-4fcd-93ce-7f4e88c3107f', 'checkbox', 'Questions 22–23', '', '<p data-start="791" data-end="822">Choose <strong data-start="798" data-end="805">TWO</strong> correct answers.</p>
<p data-start="824" data-end="839">Which <strong>TWO </strong>of the following statements are true concerning Dr Clayton’s experiments with scrub jays?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "The experiments indicated that the birds could remember how long their food had been buried"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "In the experiments, the scrub jays preferred burying moth larvae to burying peanuts"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "In the experiments, the birds were guided by the smell of the hidden food"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Scrub jays were taught by Dr Clayton to store food for future use"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "Scrub jays would rather eat certain nuts than decaying moth larvae"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a82f7215-7636-4dba-b60a-5f014bf414f5', 'ccc02ffb-54d6-4fcd-93ce-7f4e88c3107f', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p data-start="1976" data-end="2052">Complete the summary. Write <strong data-start="2004" data-end="2021">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="2059" data-end="2098"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-start="2063" data-end="2098">What is ‘true’ episodic memory?</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="2100" data-end="2514">Dr Suddendorf believes that ‘true’ episodic memory requires the ability to use the memory for the future. He cites as evidence ancient {tools} which early humans had taken some distance from where they had been originally fashioned. Dr Suddendorf’s theory is supported by brain scans showing activation of certain networks in particular areas of the brain both by episodic memory and by consideration of the future.</p>
<p data-start="2516" data-end="2832">Do non-human animals also exhibit ‘true’ episodic memory? Cebus monkeys appear to waste food once they are full, indicating that they do not plan for the future. However, in experiments, squirrel monkeys chose not to take the extra {dates} they were offered as food, in anticipation of wanting {water} soon afterwards.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ba0baa95-3705-4a57-948d-1b2f0c16edc1', '8f16efc8-db5b-430a-b56d-a12ef211ba87', 'matching', 'Question 27-30', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, A-G, in boxes 27-30 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "planning for the future."}, {"optionText": "predicting their errors."}, {"optionText": "continuing in the present situation."}, {"optionText": "recent findings on the most effective solutions to problems."}, {"optionText": "achieving a gain."}, {"optionText": "changes occurring externally."}, {"optionText": "a high level of agreement."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "K. C. Cole points out that avoiding a loss seems more important to people than", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "According to Andrew S. Grove, it can be very dangerous for companies to ignore", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Reid J. Lifset argues that environmental agencies can benefit from", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "The writer suggests that government leaders need to focus more on", "correctAnswer": "A"}]}', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1a2356cb-9816-4734-a71e-24d7016f1b0e', 'd69f9192-7cd8-46eb-87c9-721db4a66438', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23 and 24', '', '<p data-start="425" data-end="453">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="455" data-end="508">Which <strong>TWO </strong>statements summarise Monderman’s ideas?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. Rules should be regularly updated"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. Anyone can be a competent driver"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. Ineffective street furniture should be removed"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. Town centres need to be continually modernised"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. More rules make drivers behave less responsibly"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9ec94da7-4721-415f-96cf-5d94d4209c9e', 'acec8d06-41d2-4d0c-813b-a00da10ab83f', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p class="MsoNormal">Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR NUMBER</strong> for each answer.1</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: left;" align="center"><strong><span style="font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;">Building Work</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Address: 15 Hill Street</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Contact information</strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l11 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;">Name: Sally {Keyworth}</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l8 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in;">phone: 027 584 6613</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Kitchen</strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l6 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;">needs a bigger window</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l2 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in;">the kitchen is too hot – fit a {fan}</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Bathroom</strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l5 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in;">put in a {shower} on the back wall</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l9 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;">decide the {colour|color} of the small tiles later</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Outside</strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l1 level1 lfo7; tab-stops: list .5in;">put a higher {gate} in the garden</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in;">put a new {lock} on the garage door</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l10 level1 lfo9; tab-stops: list .5in;">fix the roof – it was damaged by a {storm}</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l7 level1 lfo10; tab-stops: list .5in;">fit a new rain gutter made of {plastic}</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Other information</strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l4 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: list .5in;">start date: {May 8th | 8 May | 8th May| May 8}</li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l3 level1 lfo12; tab-stops: list .5in;">security code: {AG4176}</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 1</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Morning, thanks for coming round. I’m Sally.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Morning. Um, so just before we get started, I’ll just make a few notes. So um, we’re at 15 Hill Street?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Yes, that’s right.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Okay great. And then I need to write down your contact information just for the office, you know. So first, what’s your surname please Sally?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> It’s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(1) Keyworth</strong></span>. I’ll spell that: K-E-Y-W-O-R-T-H.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> And your phone number? I’ve got that somewhere… yes, 027 584 6613.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> That’s right.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> OK Sally, so what building work would you like to have done?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well, let’s go into the kitchen first. So you see it’s quite dark in here. We’ve tried having a few lights fitted, but it hasn’t really made any difference. So what we’ve decided is the window is too small; we’d like a larger one.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> That shouldn’t be a problem. And is there anything else you’d like done in the kitchen?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well, at this time of year—I mean I shouldn’t complain really—but I wish it wasn’t so hot in here. Is there anything you can do about that?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Air conditioning?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> It’s too expensive.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> How about a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(2) fan</strong></span> then?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Yes, that would be perfect.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Alright. Oh, and what’s next Sally?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well, if we walk through into the bathroom… the thing is, when my father’s staying, he can’t use the bath. So I thought here on the back wall, I’d like you to fit a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(3) shower</strong>.</span> Is that possible?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Shouldn’t be too hard. I’ll get you some brochures because there are a few ways of doing that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Thanks. Now those tiles on the wall look new, so do you want to keep those?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Yes, the tiles are new, but actually my husband doesn’t like them. We want to change to those very small ones. But do I have to choose a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(4) colour</strong> (hoặc <strong>color</strong>) </span></span>now?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> You can do that later. I’ll get some charts for you to look at.</p>\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n<hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" />\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Now the last thing, let’s walk outside. I need to show you some things outside the house.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Right out… oh, nice garden! And the fence looks in good condition.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Yes, it’s new. But the thing is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(5) gate</strong></span>; it’s too low. You have to bend down to open it. We need something that’s higher.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Right, I’ll see to that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Then the other thing is the garage here. We had a break-in actually.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Uh yeah, I can see. Um, the door should be fine but the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(6) lock</strong>.</span></span>.. I’ll replace that shall I?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Yes thanks. Then also if you step back here and look up on the roof, you can see that it’s damaged.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Did that happen in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(7) storm</strong></span> a couple of weeks ago?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Yes, that’s right. I’ll get up there and take a look at that then. That might be quite a big job, but I’ll get back to you once I’ve had a look.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> OK. I can see that your rain gutter is broken as well. Can you fix that?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Well, I’ll need to replace it, maybe with a steel one. It’ll be stronger.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> No, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(8) plastic</strong></span> will be fine thanks. It’s cheaper.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Okay. And that’s everything I think. Is there any other information you need? What about a start date?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> Well, I’m completely booked all April, and I’ve got a job on May the 5th. That’ll be a few days, so let’s say <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(9) May 8th</strong> (hoặc <strong>8 May / 8th May</strong>).</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Okay. Now what about a key in case you’re out?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Sally:</strong> We have a security code, I’ll give you that. It’s a mix of letters and numbers. The code is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(10) AG4176</strong>.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Builder:</strong> Got that. Okay, we’ll organize some…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fece1085-9241-473f-a74c-52a96d443b06', 'd69f9192-7cd8-46eb-87c9-721db4a66438', 'radio', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. happened by chance"}, {"option_text": "B. could not be explained"}, {"option_text": "C. was made by a local newspaper"}], "question": "The discovery made in Portishead"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. risked facing legal action"}, {"option_text": "B. failed to keep people informed"}, {"option_text": "C. had to undertake complicated work"}], "question": "When they switched off the traffic lights in Bristol, local authorities"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. equally safe for drivers and pedestrians"}, {"option_text": "B. safer for drivers than for pedestrians"}, {"option_text": "C. safer for pedestrians than for drivers"}], "question": "According to research into road safety around Europe, roads in Britain are"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They were presented in an inappropriate form"}, {"option_text": "B. They were too closely based on other research"}, {"option_text": "C. They misrepresented the opinions of disabled people"}], "question": "Why does Jack criticise the findings about disabled road users?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. feel anxious about crossing the road"}, {"option_text": "B. want to change the layout of the square"}, {"option_text": "C. say that pedestrians had equal status to drivers"}], "question": "Compared to the men interviewed in Dishford, women were more likely to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. give the public clearer choices"}, {"option_text": "B. consult local people early in the design process"}, {"option_text": "C. walk more around the neighbourhood they are working in"}], "question": "According to the group ‘Living Streets’, urban planners should"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
